Text.Value: You can't go alone. I'm coming too.
I will pray anew to my Moon Mother for your health, wealth, and happiness.
Hmm. If you judge him worth the endeavour, then I will do as you say. Now that Dame Aylin has returned to the fold of time, she will need allies and interlocutors.
A wizard called Lorroakan is looking for you.
Don't pursue him, Aylin. He's dangerous.
The weasel out-weasled. Well done, my friend.
If this wizard, by your estimation, is a bungling buffoon, it may be best to let him tie himself in knots.
He seems dangerous. I think we ought to put an end to him.
Let them come, and let them find me. Dame Aylin will strike down any who seek to bring her to harm's home.
I'll come with you, then. Just in case.
Dame Aylin does not worry; she strategises.
Let us not dwell on those dark days. Their memory is a vortex within my heart that leads directly to the Hells.
He wants to cage you like Ketheric did.
Then again... it may be best to tie the knot myself.
Our closest ally will accompany me - won't you? It will be a swift and fruitful chore.
All I know is that he's put out a contract for your capture.
Do not speak false to Dame Aylin. Not after all we have endured.
Dame Aylin will make short work of this wizard - whatever his intentions.
I was just wondering what it was like in that cage of Balthazar's.
Is he indeed? Pray tell, what does he seek from Dame Aylin?
Let us travel to his chambers, his lair. We will see him undone in the style of the dead, unburied Ketheric Thorm.
Magicians and their machinations. I have had enough for an eternity.
I deceived him into thinking you're dead.
I won't let you go alone. Who knows what this wizard might have planned?
Let's take him down - together.
Hie we to this 'Lorroakan' right away. I am as eager to meet him as he is to ensnare me.
It is he who must not pursue me.
Yet... it is better to cut off the head of the snake than to let its slithering snakelings swarm us unabated. This wizard... this wizard must be held to account.
A wizard called Lorroakan was looking to capture you - I went ahead and killed him.
Your intuitions are my lodestar, darling. But consider: now that Dame Aylin has returned to the fold of time, she could use allies and interlocutors.
I will wring his neck until he's dead.
Ha! Ally mine, you continue to delight.
I think he just wants to talk. We should go find out what he wants.
But Dame Aylin's deeds are great; her presence - present. Sooner or later, he will discover that the daughter of Selûne lives.
My darling, we agreed you'd scout for the nearest Selûnite enclave this very night. Let us divide our efforts, all the sooner to be reunited.
Oh, I hope he tries. Please, Lorroakan, come to me with your magicks and your flaccid charms. Attempt to lay one hairy finger upon Dame Aylin, daughter of Selûne most high.

EditorData.NodeContext: Low fury, daring Lorroakan to try to capture and cage her.

Text.Value: I'm coming with you. I'd like to get a few licks in myself.
The beast!
He seemed a braggart and a fool - I wouldn't worry about it.
He put a bounty out for your capture and now there is a violent mercenary looking for you.
Aylin, I'm not sure about this. Something doesn't feel right.
Don't pursue him, Aylin. He could be dangerous.
I must face the villain, nose-to-nose and sword-to-sword. I hope I can count on your aid in the fight to come.
Troubles make a poor supper. Do not hesitate to spit yours out.
Ho! His end will be one more strand in the great braid of our friendship.
Leave.
It's nothing - we'll talk later.
Mother's Milk - your visage speaks of ill tidings. Speak, ally mine: what troubles you?
Leave.

EditorData.logicalname: Leave for if Lorroakan is alive

Synopsis: The avatar talks to Nightsong in camp after meeting Lorroakan and seeing how he is looking for her. The player explains what he knows, which will trigger nightsong to leave to camp to confront Lorroakan.
